As you can see, en_pp were all 0, which was absolutely incorrect. It should be 1 after cycle 1.
And I looked into the cpp code, I could find the code related to the assignment `en_pp = pp[1]` in Vdemo__Slow.cpp
```cpp
void Vdemo::_settle__TOP__2(Vdemo__Syms* __restrict vlSymsp) {
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+    Vdemo::_settle__TOP__2\n"); );
    Vdemo* const __restrict vlTOPp VL_ATTR_UNUSED = vlSymsp->TOPp;
    // Body
    vlTOPp->t__DOT__U_SUB__DOT__pp[0U] = 1U;
    vlTOPp->en_pp = vlTOPp->t__DOT__U_SUB__DOT__pp[1U]; // code related to assignment.
}
```
But I failed to find any code related to the assignment `en_pp = pp[1]` in _combo_ function or _sequent_ function.
What's more, I studied some source code, maybe the assignment had been deleted in V3Order by marking it as delete domain?

What's your opinion?


Thanks.
